MVC
Very popular upon two things

01. Well represents the concept of seperation of concerns
02. Very easy to explain. easy to learn & easy to impelement

Seperation of Concerns

M - holds the app state/ data / Domain
DBs, Repositories, Files, Clouds etc

C - receives input from view, change app state upon business logic
    collborate between V & M
    
V - represent app state
    take inputs from user
    
    
Massive View Controller

earned the nickname, as Controller might end up with lots of code.
Becasue Views represent app state, models holds data & all the other work
is done by Controller.


    
